  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n1) \"Gas Limit\"  \r\nwhen I erase value in \"Gas Limit\" it is automatically set to `0`\r\n2) \"Gas Value\"  \r\nif I erase one char in value `1.00001`, I've got `1` instead of `1.0000`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1) value is empty, can type the desired value\r\n2) `1.0000`, so I can continue editing value; or if initial value was `5.7`, I want to get `5.`, not `5` \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n1) value is immediately replaced by 0, and I should erase 0 in order to type desired value\r\n2) `1`\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n*1) Gas Limit*\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Tap on Wallet\r\n- Tap on \"Send transaction\"\r\n- Tap on Advanced\r\n- Erase default value in \"Gas Limit\"\r\n\r\n*2) Gas Price*\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Tap on Wallet\r\n- Tap on \"Send transaction\"\r\n- Tap on Advanced\r\n- Type in Gas Price value with decimal part (i.e. `1.01` or `1.000008`, some value when last char is cut - should be any whole number without decimals) \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: nightly 01/06/2018\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n* TF Session:  https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8413233/sessions/195/?accessToken=QIoNf6hQuDDRYU4tP53jtF9NphE\r\n1) Gas Limit: 00:40 - 00:50\r\n2) Gas Price: 01:10 - 01:15\r\n\r\n\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8413233/sessions/195/?accessToken=QIoNf6hQuDDRYU4tP53jtF9NphE\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.19 (6026) @195</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
